So `rollup (Tree.leaf x :: t :: ts)` would be `foldl1 (fun u v ↦ node u v) (Tree.leaf x) (t :: ts)`.
This fold would process `t :: ts`:
- Start with `Tree.leaf x`
- `foldl1` applies `fun u v ↦ node u v` to `Tree.leaf x` and `t`, resulting in `node (Tree.leaf x) t`
- Then applies `fun u v ↦ node u v` to `node (Tree.leaf x) t` and `ts`, resulting in `node (node (Tree.leaf x) t) ts`

So `rollup (Tree.leaf x :: t :: ts) = node (node (Tree.leaf x) t) ts`.

Then `spine (rollup (Tree.leaf x :: t :: ts))` is `spine (node (node (Tree.leaf x) t) ts)`.
By definition of `spine`:
