By the recursive definition of `spine`, this is `spine (List.foldl (fun u v => .node u v) (Tree.leaf x) ts) ++ [t]`.
By the induction hypothesis, this is `([Tree.leaf x] ++ ts) ++ [t]`.
And `[Tree.leaf x] ++ t :: ts` is `[Tree.leaf x] ++ [t] ++ ts`.
So we need to show `([Tree.leaf x] ++ ts) ++ [t] = [Tree.leaf x] ++ [t] ++ ts`.
This is true by associativity of list concatenation.

