`foldl1 .node (node (leaf x) t) ts` is the fold operation applied to `ts` with the initial value `node (leaf x) t`.
If we denote `F = foldl1 .node (node (leaf x) t)`, then `F ts` is the result of the fold.
The definition of `foldl1` is `List.foldl f acc`.
