This looks like it can be proved by induction on `ys`.
Base case: `ys = []`
`spine (foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) []) = spine (node X t)`
`= spine (node (leaf x) t)`
`= spine (leaf x) ++ [t]`
`= [leaf x] ++ [t]`
This matches the right side `[leaf x] ++ [t] ++ []`.

Inductive step: Assume it holds for `zs`, prove for `z₁ :: zs`
Assume `spine (foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) zs) = [leaf x] ++ [t] ++ zs`
We need to show `spine (foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) (z₁ :: zs)) = [leaf x] ++ [t] ++ (z₁ :: zs)`
`foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) (z₁ :: zs)`
`= (fun x y ↦ node x y) (foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) zs) z₁`
`= node (foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) zs) z₁`

Then, `spine` applied to this:
`spine (node (foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) zs) z₁)`
`= spine (foldl (fun x y ↦ node x y) (node X t) zs) ++ [z₁]`
By the inductive hypothesis:
`= ([leaf x] ++ [t] ++ zs) ++ [z₁]`
`= [leaf x] ++ [t] ++ zs ++ [z₁]`
`= [leaf x] ++ [t] ++ (z₁ :: zs)`
This is what we need.

So, we can prove this helper lemma by induction.

Now, let's write the proof in Lean.
```tactics
import Fad.Chapter1
import Fad.«Chapter1-Ex»
import Fad.Chapter3
import Fad.Chapter5
import Fad.Chapter6
import Fad.Chapter7

namespace Chapter8

namespace S1

/- 8.1 Minimum-height trees -/

open Chapter5.Mergesort (halve length_halve_fst length_halve_snd pairWith)
open Chapter1 (wrap unwrap single until' concatMap)
open Chapter6 (foldl1)
open Chapter7 (minWith)

inductive Tree (α : Type) : Type where
 | leaf : α → Tree α
 | node : Tree α → Tree α → Tree α
 deriving Repr, Inhabited


def Tree.size {α : Type} : Tree α → Nat
 | Tree.leaf _ => 1
 | Tree.node t₁ t₂ => t₁.size + t₂.size


def Tree.height {α : Type} : Tree α → Nat
 | Tree.leaf _ => 0
 | Tree.node t₁ t₂ => Nat.max t₁.height t₂.height + 1


def Tree.fringe {α : Type} : Tree α → List α
 | Tree.leaf x => [x]
 | Tree.node t₁ t₂ => t₁.fringe ++ t₂.fringe


